<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_Beginner_BuildMode_BasicBuilding" s="314006">
  <T n="name">0xE96CB29C<!--String: "Basic Building"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\Beginner\Beginner_BasicBuilding_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:a524d65717abd8a0</T>
      <T n="text">0xE36FDC1E<!--String: "To <b><font color='#199C2C'>modify</font></b> and <b><font color='#199C2C'>upgrade</font></b> your home, there are some essential <b><font color='#199C2C'>Build Mode tools</font></b> you should know about.\n\nSelecting an existing Room by clicking on its floor or walls reveals arrows that allow you to <b><font color='#199C2C'>change the shape</font></b> of the room. You can also change <b><font color='#199C2C'>Wall Height</font></b> this way!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\Beginner\Beginner_BasicBuilding_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:a524d65717abd8a3</T>
      <T n="text">0x53EAA049<!--String: "You can also make <b><font color='#199C2C'>new Rooms</font></b> by using the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Wall and Room Tools</font></b> found in the Walls and Empty Rooms category. Simply click, drag, and release to place a new Wall or Room!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\Beginner\Beginner_BasicBuilding_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:a524d65717abd8a2</T>
      <T n="text">0x709AB56D<!--String: "To allow Sims and light to enter your new Room, it needs <b><font color='#199C2C'>Doors</font></b> and <b><font color='#199C2C'>Windows</font></b>, found in the Doors and Windows Catalogs respectively. They are sorted by Wall Height.\n\nSelect a Door or Window from the Catalog, move the cursor to a wall, and click to place. The Door or Window will snap to the Wall if there’s enough space."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\Beginner\Beginner_BasicBuilding_4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:a524d65717abd8a5</T>
      <T n="text">0xCA7D8804<!--String: "When you add or extend a Room, you probably want to adjust the house’s <b><font color='#199C2C'>Roof</font></b> to match.\n\nYou can either select an existing Roof piece and use the <b><font color='#199C2C'>resizing arrows</font></b>, or place a new <b><font color='#199C2C'>Roof piece</font></b> from the Roof menu."--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
  <L n="tags">
    <E>Lesson_Beginner_BuildMode</E>
